                            <comment id="12463" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Mon, 28 Feb 2005 02:35:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Indeed, we should never pass a value of 0 to setQueryTimeout. I&apos;ve adapted ResourceHolderSupport accordingly, throwing an explicit TransactionTimedOutException if the time-to-live falls below 1.&lt;/p&gt;

